</tr></thead>
<tbody><tr id="_83a1695d-0eb1-5a4c-ce06-a0c582ed38e1"><td id="_563d9765-ffd8-ebc4-1f9b-d3d19bfe390b" valign="top" align="left"><stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle displaystyle="false"><mn>2466061413187035</mn></mstyle></math><asciimath>2466061413187035</asciimath></stem></td>
<td id="_a672433c-5449-55fa-8d61-c8739c81f958" valign="top" align="center"><stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle displaystyle="false"><mn>10</mn></mstyle></math><asciimath>10</asciimath></stem></td>
<td id="_20f1ce55-1448-b37c-57bc-02cfe8442650" valign="top" align="center"><eref type="inline" bibitemid="parthey" citeas="[2]"/></td>
</tr><tr id="_f0974b1f-d16d-8224-a5a6-251805ed2738"><td id="_17c15c5f-abaf-3ce7-2265-31447f3f4d5f" valign="top" align="left"><stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle displaystyle="false"><mn>2466061413187018</mn></mstyle></math><asciimath>2466061413187018</asciimath></stem></td>
<td id="_c46ba9d3-e023-5593-6ac2-4306aa827c83" valign="top" align="center"><stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle displaystyle="false"><mn>11</mn></mstyle></math><asciimath>11</asciimath></stem></td>
<td id="_6015939f-bd30-480a-1348-3f6576af10ce" valign="top" align="center"><eref type="inline" bibitemid="matveev" citeas="[3]"/></td>
</tr></tbody>
</table>

<p id="_98f97744-1d8c-6e5f-112c-a1b7ba83abb7">as a weighted mean of the above values divided by two.</p>

<p id="_682dbf6a-3ad8-f6e6-28d1-523425d800c6">Given the noticeable drift of the values of the past measurements <eref type="inline" bibitemid="matveev" citeas="[3]"/> and the fact that the values come from a single laboratory the CCTF considered it prudent to attribute an increased standard uncertainty by a factor of three.</p>
</clause>


